node.accessibility_caption: Photo by JJ_MOBILEPHOTOGRAPHY on September 03, 2021. May be an image of nature and grass.

node.text:
D.O.F. (Depth of Field) 
👉👉Swipe through the pics
.
😃👋 It’s Kel @mackelleen here!
Before using Instagram, I never heard of the term D.O.F.and I was confused by it for quite a while. 🤔
Sometimes, it’s used casually, which can cause more confusion.🤷🏼‍♀️

‼️Don’t forget to tag your mobile images that demonstrate DOF, for our Weeklong Challenge!!!‼️
👀See our post from this morning! (Friday Sept 3)
.
🤚🚫1st - what it’s NOT (sorry!):
Technically, Depth of Field is NOT about how close the in-focus object is to the lens.
(When using a cellphone, this does impact the DOF, but it’s not what defines it.)
💎Rather, it is the depth of the scene that is in focus.
.
1️⃣👉 🍞Think of the image as slices of bread in a loaf, and you are a little creature eating through it, heel to heel! 🐭🍞
‼️But the 🐭 is only allowed to eat the slices that are in focus! 🔎🤔
...
👉In this image, the slices of “bread” are:
☘️🌱first slice is clover/grass
➿then a feather
🌱more🌱, more🌱, more🌱,
🚙🚐vehicles
and eventually,
⛅️🌅the clouds/sunset is the last piece of bread.
.
❗️Most cellphones will automatically shoot DEEP depth of field - attempting to get everything in focus.❗️
.
👉Swipe to next “page” in this post😉

Let’s compare the two sides on this image....
2️⃣🔹👉On the LEFT side, with deep DOF, you can see MANY slices in focus. (Grass🌱 grass🌱 grass🌱 vehicles🚐🚙, and the sunset🌅!)
.
The 🐭 would eat MANY slices of bread! This is DEEP depth of field.
.
3️⃣🔸👉On the RIGHT side, with shallow DOF, you only see one slice in focus, really! (The feather➿ and a tiny bit of 🌱 under it.)
.
The 🐭 would only eat one piece of bread, right? This is SHALLOW depth of field.
.
👉Swipe to 4th page!

4️⃣ I have included another photo #4, which shows a medium depth of field.
🔺Notice on the fourth photo, the feather ➿is not in focus, and neither are the vehicles🚙🚐/ sunset🌅.
👉The only part in focus is the 🌱🌱🌱 between the feather and the vehicles.
So, not deep, and not shallow - MEDIUM depth of field (D.O.F.).🤔
.
We can’t wait to see your posts for this weeklong challenge!!! 😃🎉

Check out the prior post for challenge rules!! ‼️

node.text:
Hello and Happy “Challenge Announcement” Day, Fam! 🥳 🎊 

We have a very special WEEKLONG CHALLENGE that begins today. 
Our weeklong challenges are hosted by our own jj_mp team. Our mods will be selecting at least 1 winning submission to feature from the challenge tag each day. 🎉🎉🎉
You can tag to the challenge all week! The challenge closes on Thursday, September 9th at 9pm Eastern time.❗️
.
👉👉Check out our next post today, if the idea of Depth of Field (DOF) is a little fuzzy! 😃
.
.
Theme: “Depth of Field”
#jj_mp_iheart_alfresco_photos 
.
‼️Challenge Rules:‼️
▶️ MUST be following @jj_mobilephotography
▶️ Specify which mobile device you used

▶️ Tag #jj_mobilephoto_dof

▶️New or old photos okay (we encourage new ones so get out there and shoot!)
▶️No previously featured (here on jj_mp) photos please
▶️ Don't forget to 1,2,3: For every 1 picture you post, comment on 2 others in the tag, and like 3 others.  This is also about building community and connecting with others.

node.text:
Marika highlights this serene beauty as her 5th and final selection from the weekend. Huge thanks to you, Marika, for the wonderful theme, selections, and being such a joy to work with! Hey, jj mobile fam! Please help us thank Marika for such an awesome job. We invite you to also check out her gallery and show her some jj mp appreciation! Here are her thoughts on the selection and challenge:
.

“Rosemary’s green forest and pure lake with the fallen tree leading the eye to floating clouds is calming my soul ☁️ Hope you can feel it too! Congratulations Rosemary 💚”. 

Huge thanks to you all absolutely talented and lovely people who wanted to take part this weekend’s JJMP Challenge “Reflections of nature” 🤍 It was so hard for me to choose from all those wonderful pictures ❤️ Thank you for giving so much this weekend ❤️ And thanks again Dee for this opportunity, I enjoyed every moment! Happy Autumn to ya all ❤️ - @marikahv
